    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-20T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-20T01:00:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811B.20/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-20T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 20, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 20—12:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For the United States High Commissioner:<note n="76" xml:id="d586fn76">Francis B.
                        Sayre, at Manila.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Chinese Foreign Office has informed Embassy of the Chinese Government’s
                            desire that the Philippine authorities permit the organization in the
                            Philippines of a Chinese volunteer corps to fight side by side with
                            Americans and Filipinos. Foreign Office stresses beneficial
                            psychological effect upon large population in the Islands and requests
                            that you approach the Philippine Government.”<note n="77"
                                xml:id="d586fn77">Ambassador Gauss was instructed on December 27 to
                                inform the Chinese Foreign Office that the offer was greatly
                                appreciated and was receiving active consideration.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Manila; repeated to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
